{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.20",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 20 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:1",
      "text": "Wine is a mocker, strong drink a brawler; and whoever is led astray by it is not wise.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:2",
      "text": "The dread wrath of a king is like the growling of a lion; he who provokes him to anger forfeits his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:3",
      "text": "It is an honor for a man to keep aloof from strife; but every fool will be quarreling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:4",
      "text": "The sluggard does not plow in the autumn; he will seek at harvest and have nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:5",
      "text": "The purpose in a man's mind is like deep water, but a man of understanding will draw it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:6",
      "text": "Many a man proclaims his own loyalty, but a faithful man who can find?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:7",
      "text": "A righteous man who walks in his integrity— blessed are his sons after him!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:8",
      "text": "A king who sits on the throne of judgment winnows all evil with his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:9",
      "text": "Who can say, “I have made my heart clean; I am pure from my sin”?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:10",
      "text": "Diverse weights and diverse measures are both alike an abomination to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:11",
      "text": "Even a child makes himself known by his acts, whether what he does is pure and right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:12",
      "text": "The hearing ear and the seeing eye, the Lord has made them both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:13",
      "text": "Love not sleep, lest you come to poverty; open your eyes, and you will have plenty of bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:14",
      "text": "“It is bad, it is bad,” says the buyer; but when he goes away, then he boasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:15",
      "text": "There is gold, and abundance of costly stones; but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:16",
      "text": "Take a man's garment when he has given surety for a stranger, and hold him in pledge when he gives surety for foreigners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:17",
      "text": "Bread gained by deceit is sweet to a man, but afterward his mouth will be full of gravel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:18",
      "text": "Plans are established by counsel; by wise guidance wage war.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:19",
      "text": "He who goes about gossiping reveals secrets; therefore do not associate with one who speaks foolishly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:20",
      "text": "If one curses his father or his mother, his lamp will be put out in utter darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:21",
      "text": "An inheritance gotten hastily in the beginning will in the end not be blessed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:22",
      "text": "Do not say, “I will repay evil”; wait for the Lord, and he will help you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:23",
      "text": "Diverse weights are an abomination to the Lord, and false scales are not good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:24",
      "text": "A man's steps are ordered by the Lord; how then can man understand his way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:25",
      "text": "It is a snare for a man to say rashly, “It is holy,” and to reflect only after making his vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:26",
      "text": "A wise king winnows the wicked, and drives the wheel over them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:27",
      "text": "The spirit of man is the lamp of the Lord, searching all his innermost parts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:28",
      "text": "Loyalty and faithfulness preserve the king, and his throne is upheld by righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:29",
      "text": "The glory of young men is their strength, but the beauty of old men is their gray hair.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.20.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:30",
      "text": "Blows that wound cleanse away evil; strokes make clean the innermost parts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
